{"id":91131,"title":"Management of major burns: rehabilitation and recovery.","abstract":"Management of major burns is complex and challenging because of the serious and often life-threatening nature of the injuries and associated systemic complications. Therefore, the burn care practitioner requires comprehensive knowledge of the treatment options and procedures that may be used to maximise patient rehabilitation and recovery. This article aims to discuss the latest evidence in burn care, and the treatments and interventions that a patient may receive following a major burn injury. ","date":"2014-02-19","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24547864","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.651095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.585652,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Knowledge","weight":0.370748,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knowledge"},{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.290163,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Burn","weight":0.0646925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burn"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.0604488,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Injury","weight":0.0508378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injury"},{"name":"Evidence","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence"},{"name":"Obstetrics","weight":0.0219197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obstetrics"},{"name":"Academic major","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_major"},{"name":"Option (finance)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Option_(finance)"},{"name":"Complexity","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complexity"},{"name":"Nature","w